<br/>
<div class="grid-container tutorial-container">
  <h1 class = "tutorial-title">How to Play:</h1>
  <ul class="tutorial-list">
    <p>The name of the game is guessing the secret word, and you only get 5 guesses.
    </p>
    <p>For instance, if the secret word was "Haggle", and you guesssed "Honest",
    </p>
    <p>the letters will be highlighted one of 3 colors:
    </p>
    <div>
      <div class="grid-x tutorial-content">
        <div class="guess-letter-tile"><br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="correct-letter-spot">
            h
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guess-letter-tile">
          <br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="Incorrect">
            o
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guess-letter-tile">
          <br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="Incorrect">
            n
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guess-letter-tile">
          <br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="correct-letter">
            e
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guess-letter-tile">
          <br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="Incorrect">
            s
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guess-letter-tile">
          <br>
          <div class="cell guess-display" id="Incorrect">
            t
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br/>
    <p>If the letter is highlighted yellow, it's in the word, but it's in the incorrect spot.
    </p>
    <p>If the letter is highlighted green, it's in the word, and it's in the correct spot.
    </p>
    <p>However, if the letter is highlighted gray, it's not in the word at all.
    </p>
    <li>Good luck, and have fun!
    </li>
  </ul>
  <div class="cell tutorial-button">
  <%= link_to "Play!", new_session_path, class: ' cell button-19 button-forms' %>
  </div>
  <br/>
</div>
